BASENAME(1)                    User Commands                    BASENAME(1)

NAME
    basename - strip directory and suffix from a file name

SYNOPSIS
    basename NAME [SUFFIX]
    basename OPTION... NAME...

DESCRIPTION
    Print NAME with any leading directory components removed. If SUFFIX is
    given and is a trailing part of the result, it is removed too.

        basename /usr/share/man/tail   ->  tail
        basename /a/b/c.txt .txt       ->  c

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils basename(1), ported to Horus and run
    as a ring-3 program from /bin/basename.

OPTIONS
    -a           treat every argument as a NAME
    -s SUFFIX    remove a trailing SUFFIX (implies -a)
    -z           separate output with NUL rather than newline

    Run `basename --help` for the full option list.

EXIT STATUS
    0 on success, non-zero on error.

SEE ALSO
    dirname(1), hier(7)
